text: Finsk Tidskrift (meaning Finnish Journal in English) is a Swedish language cultural magazine based in Finland. Founded in 1876 it is the oldest cultural publication in Finland. The founder was Carl Gustaf Estlander, a Finnish academic and cultural activist. He also served as the editor-in-chief of the magazine from its start in 1876 to 1886. Finsk Tidskrift is published eight times a year.
